mutant: m038_live_op_path_gate_skipped
target: internal/ingest/live/events.go
failure-mode: |
  convertCommit's per-op #197 validation gate is disabled (validateOpPath
  result ignored), so spec-invalid op paths — $-prefixed collections that
  can shadow the sentinel index, null-byte/oversized rkeys — archive
  verbatim instead of dropping. Models the validation-skipped regression
  class: a refactor that accidentally bypasses the gate.
expected-detection: |
  The #204 adversarial phase emits live op lies every run: the expected
  event log excludes ledgered lie rows, so an archived lie fails the
  steady-state multiset compare as an extra observed event; the
  adversarial drop-counter floors also go unmet. Default tier (red-first
  verified at introduction: extra "bad\x00key" row).
expected-tier: default
tiers: default,stress

